###

@baseUrl = https://express.dhanifudin.com
@token = REPLACE_WITH_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN


### 1) Create Snap transaction token — success (200)

POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/snap/token HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "order_id": "ORDER-001",
  "gross_amount": 50000,
  "item_details": [
    {
      "id": "item-1",
      "price": 50000,
      "quantity": 1,
      "name": "Example Item"
    }
  ],
  "customer_details": {
    "first_name": "Budi",
    "last_name": "Santoso",
    "email": "budi@example.com",
    "phone": "08111222333"
  }
}


### 2) Create Snap token — missing order_id (400)

POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/snap/token HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "gross_amount": 50000
}


### 3) Create Snap token — no auth (401)

POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/snap/token HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "ORDER-001",
  "gross_amount": 50000
}


### 4) Midtrans payment notification webhook (no auth required)

POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/notification HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "ORDER-001",
  "status_code": "200",
  "gross_amount": "50000.00",
  "signature_key": "MIDTRANS_SIGNATURE",
  "transaction_status": "settlement",
  "fraud_status": "accept",
  "payment_type": "credit_card"
}


### 5) Get transaction status — success (200)

GET {{baseUrl}}/payments/status/ORDER-001 HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 6) Get transaction status — no auth (401)

GET {{baseUrl}}/payments/status/ORDER-001 HTTP/1.1
